What a great beer! It's full of light tasty citrus notes and flavors! It's tasty but very light and drinkable! Totally a session beer that brings the flavors.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is my first time trying a dark sour and it is not a disappointment! Almost black in color this beer has a nose for the sour. A dark beer for sure but the aging of three years in cab barrels turns this dark beer into a great sour full of flavors from coffee to wine and in between! 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

I love this beer, it is simple yet full of flavor. The open air fermenting really lends to a unique and tasty beer, that leans to a sour but is not overpowered with unnecessary fruits or off flavors. A true blast from the past!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Best beer made by Pyramid! Nice hops and a light citrus flavor create an enjoyable beer. At 6% abv this is close to a session beer with the flavor of a full bodied IPA.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice brown color that pours well. Carbonated nicely, drinks relatively smoothly for a beer of this style. Somewhat sweet for my liking but all in all a good beer!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours nicely and fills in with a nice head. Dark blonde in color with a good bit of carbonation. Smells and tastes of fresh grass and Meyer lemons. Easy to drink and stays refreshing on the tongue.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not a bad beer for the price, light with an airy hoppy flavor that favors bitter over malty. This beer is on and off the tongue quickly which makes for a good light beer to drink during a sunny day at the cafe. Not the best beer but if you are looking for a cheap light beer this might be a good option.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice brown color with a stable airy head. Well carbonated and true to its style this beer is enjoyable top to bottom. Tastes of nuts, sweet potato, and quality malts. This beer starts and finishes sweet and is well balanced for even flavors throughout. 

Bottoms Up!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

True to its style this blonde beer has a light golden hue that pours well with a solid but not sturdy head. At first taste your palate enjoys a bit of bitterness but that quickly gives way to an overwhelming sweetness that is defined by tastes of brown sugar, roasted cashews, and syrups. The sweetness lingers on the tongue but balances nicely over time. Overall an enjoyable well executed blonde beer, however it is a bit too sweet for my tastes.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
